n to be<br />&gt; page-aligned. <br /><br />Note that I'll probably use the "ALIGN(4096)" thing for other things too<br />in the near future (getting rid of some of the data stuff in "head.S", so<br />a linker that doesn't honour the alignment restrictions will break badly<br />because that non-alignment simply cannot be fixed up at run-time. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
